node.text:
Working on this painting was the first time I ever documented the full process of a painting from start to finish. Looking back on it, it’s amazing to see where it started and where it ended. Making art can be really hard, not just in terms of technical skill but in terms of mental fortitude, it’s something I’ve been talking to a lot of artists about lately. Creating doesn’t end up being this beautiful, relaxing, freeing time, instead it’s often a huge mental battle. You’re constantly berating yourself when things aren’t going right, debating giving up, contemplating throwing the piece in the trash, you’ve ruined it, you’re a failure, you’ll never be as good as the people you admire so why try? I spent a lot of time working on this painting saying those exact things to myself. It wasn’t even until the very end that I even started to feel ok about the painting, but having this image of the first layer to look back on helped give me perspective that it really did come a long way. And hey maybe it’s not too terrible after all?
As artists we can really tunnel vision in on our own work and see every blemish and flaw and every way that it didn’t come out exactly as we intended that we can fail to see how it really looks. I think it’s important to know that you’re not alone in this,  it doesn’t make you less of an artist to experience these feelings, most all artists experience it. You don’t suddenly become a professional and all self doubt washes away, it will always be there. Your ability to work despite it, to be strong and push that negative voice away, tell it that it’s wrong, you can create, you aren’t failing, all art looks like an absolute mess when it’s in process, it’s normal, is ultimately the key to your growth and success as a creator. It’s also so important to realize that the way you see your art and the way others see your art aren’t the same. 
If you’ve been staring at something for 20 hours of course you’re going to know it’s every imperfection, you can have dysmorphia about your own art. Others will look at your art and see nothing but beauty and sometimes you need to let them be your eyes. Keep creating even when it’s hard it’s so important ❤️

I’m excited to announce I’ve teamed up with @bubblehouse to host a #drawthisinyourstyle challenge. There are physical prizes for this one including a few of the limited edition glitch girl pins that I have left, (swipe to see the prizes). The winners will be chosen at random so anyone who participates has a chance to win no matter what your skill level is. 

For anyone not familiar with @bubblehouse it’s a really cool app that allows you to post your art in more interactive ways including with before and after sliders (there’s an example of that on the last slide) and process sliders that show the progress of the whole piece. It’s a super cool app and I’d recommend it to anyone creative even if they’re not interested in this event. So-

Here’s how to enter! You can join on here or on the bubblehouse app or both! (Check my post on bubblehouse for the rules there)

1.) Create this in your style! You can draw it, 3D model it, photograph it etc. all styles are accepted!
 
2.) Upload your piece and include a video of it being used with a bubblehouse module! You have to have the bubblehouse app to do this, show a video of your piece with either the before/after slider or the process slider. (Your phone should have a built in screen recording setting for anyone who doesn’t know how to do this or there are screengrab apps you can use)

3.) Make sure to use the hashtag #lemonredraw2021 when you post.

4.) once you’re done comment ‘done’ along with which prize pack you want to win!

As I said before winners will be selected at random so all skill levels are invited to join. I’ll be creating a board on my bubblehouse page to share favorites as well. The deadline is September 30th. Some things to remember, if your profile is set to private I cannot see your entry even if you use the hashtag. Only entries posted to your page count I can’t accept entries via DM. Excited to see what you guys create!

#drawthisinyourstyle #dtiys #lemon #rainbow #sticker #art #artist #kawaii #anime #manga #cute #pinkhair

node.text:
I’m beyond pleased to announce that my shop is officially live! You can find it in the link in my bio! 

Being able to finally open this shop is my birthday gift to myself. It’s been so much work to get this all going but I’m really excited to have the shop finally open again. Last time it officially opened with a full stock like this was almost a year ago now. I’m thrilled to no longer have to feel overwhelmed about packaging every time I get orders now, honestly I could cry it’s such a big deal. The inventory would take up my whole house and I’d be walking through a sea of packaging and trying to get orders out fast while still managing making art, answering emails and patreon messages and going to meetings and so many other things, it was just too much. Being an artist is amazing but it’s also doing 20 different full time jobs all by yourself sometimes. Being able to get some help is such a necessity but oftentimes difficult to achieve so I can’t tell you how relieved I feel now to finally have my product in a fulfillment center and let the professionals do the shipping.
Anyway, I hope there are some things in there you guys like! And if you have requests for new products please let me know. And once again so sorry to everyone in the UK I promise I’m working as fast as I can to get all the VAT tax stuff worked out so I can ship to you I know it’s frustrating.

Happy shopping you guys and thanks so much for supporting my art!

Hello everyone! I have an official date and time for the shop launch!
The shop will be going live September 8th at 1PM pst (I’m excited, so I’m launching it on my birthday)

The shop drop will include another limited edition pin, the rainbow glitter headspace pin individually numbered on the back 1-200 (shown on the last slide). The last limited pin went really fast so if you want to grab one, be sure to be there when it opens. I’ll also have a few original sketches for sale.
Some info:
- This shop drop includes all shop items, including prints, stickers, pins, totes, shirts body pillows etc. It has not been open like this since November of 2020!

-If you’re one of my patrons you’ll be receiving early access to the store so you can shop at your leisure, I’ve also launched a patreon secret store where you can now purchase past patreon rewards, be on the lookout for a patreon update that includes the password ❤️.

- I haven’t figured out VAT tax yet unfortunately, so I’m sad to say I can’t ship to the UK at the moment but I promise I’m working on changing that in the future.

I think that’s all the info, I’ll set a countdown in my story as it gets closer to the date. If there’s any more questions you have let me know! Otherwise I’m very excited to finally be able to do this! It’s been a long time in the making

Some of you might remember this one from way back in 2018! I made it as part of a giveaway so somebody out there has the original of this and I hope they’re enjoying it ❤️For some reason when I made this I didn’t think it was going to be very well liked, so when I shipped it off I didn’t even bother to take a professional picture to make it into a print or anything like that. Years later I found out that not only did a bunch of people love it but my bf informed me that it’s always been his favorite piece often and that he was super sad I gave it away. Ever since then I wanted to remake it for him so it’s been sitting on my agenda for a while now and I’m really happy I got a moment to do it. I struggled with this one a bit but I think it turned out really pretty. You can swipe to see the original to compare and contrast ❤️
